title: Pa. Girls: Pa. girls: Phoenixville rallies past Pope John Paul II
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Catholic Academies. Shea Tomlinson, Erica DeCandido and Kendall Seifert each had one goal and one assist to lead Gwynedd Mercy to a 5-0 victory over visiting Merion Mercy.
Grace DiGiovanni had a goal and an assist in the first half of Mount St. Joseph's 2-1 win at St. Basil. 
Catholic League. Kate Henesey scored three times to lead Lansdale Catholic to a 5-1 victory over visiting St. Hubert. 
Ches-Mont. Jenna Moser scored two goals as West Chester Rustin clinched the American Division title with a 7-0 win at Coatesville. 
Morgan Mancuso and Shannon Moore scored two goals each to lead visiting West Chester East past Great Valley, 5-0. 
Sarah Shirk scored in the second half to give Oxford a 1-0 victory at Avon Grove. 
Gina Peraino scored two goals in Downingtown West's 3-0 win at Bishop Shanahan. 
Dayla Barnes and Addy Zandi scored to lead West Chester Henderson to a 2-1 triumph at Sun Valley. 
Central. Lexie Sutton scored four minutes before halftime, and Lower Merion held on for a 1-0 win at Ridley. 
Inter-Ac. Lydia Bartosh paired two goals with two assists in Agnes Irwin's 5-2 win over visiting Springside Chestnut Hill. Kristin Burnetta added two goals and one assist. 
Sophie Axenroth had two goals and one assist as host Germantown Academy stayed unbeaten in league play with a 5-0 win over Baldwin. 
Public. Mekayla Baum and Aliyyah Miller both had hat tricks as host Girls High dispatched Washington, 8-1. 
Suburban One National. Camryn Lexow scored twice to lead host Abington to a 5-0 win over Bensalem. Field Hockey Becca Inzer recorded a hat trick in the first 28 minutes of Downingtown West's 4-2 Ches-Mont win at Bishop Shanahan.
Elsewhere in the Ches-Mont, Grace Nelson's first-half goal decided visiting West Chester Rustin's 1-0 victory over Coatesville. 
Bicentennial. Olivia Succi scored three times to lead Lower Moreland to a 5-1 win at Bristol. 
Catholic Academies. Megan DuVernois deflected a corner off the goalie with 22 minutes left to give host Gwynedd Mercy a 1-0 win over Merion Mercy. 
Annina Iacobucci scored four goals as Villa Maria handled visiting Sacred Heart, 12-2. Megan Vermeil had a hat trick. 
Central. Casey Allen scored three times as Conestoga cruised past Penncrest, 10-0, at home. 
Inter-Ac. Quinn Maguire and Mary Kate Neff knocked in three goals apiece as Notre Dame breezed by Penn Charter, 11-0, on the road. 
Pioneer. Emily Owens and Emily Sayre scored for Methacton in its 2-1 home win over Owen J. Roberts. Golf Council Rock North's Madeline Herr defeated Maddie Sager of Owen J. Roberts in a playoff to claim the District 1 Class AAA championship at Turtle Creek Golf Course.
Both golfers finished with a two-day total of 3-under-par 140. 
Herr trailed Sager by 3 strokes entering the day. 
Mount St. Joseph won the team title. 
Radnor's Brynn Walker, the defending state champion, and Samantha Yao of Conestoga tied for third with 142. Coatesville's Samantha Staudt placed fifth with 145. 
New Hope-Solebury's Nina Kouchi shot 156 to win the AA title. Gwynedd Mercy took the team crown. 
District 12 Championship. Archbishop Wood's Harley Brown (9-over 79) and St. Hubert's Morgan Kodluk (98) qualified for Eastern regionals as the top girls' finishers on Phil-Mont CC's South Course.
